bug.short_desc: [abrt] opendmarc: mlfi_connect(): opendmarc killed by SIGSEGV
bug.cf_doc_type: If docs needed, set a value

long_desc.thetext:
Description of problem: OpenDMARC on Fedora 25 seems to consistently crash a few minutes after it starts (not sure if it's a time-based thing, or just that it crashes on certain problematic messages or after handling a certain number of messages).
Version-Release number of selected component: opendmarc-1.3.2-0.3.beta0.fc25
Additional info: reporter: libreport-2.8.0 backtrace_rating: 4 cmdline: /usr/sbin/opendmarc -c /etc/opendmarc.conf -P /var/run/opendmarc/opendmarc.pid crash_function: mlfi_connect executable: /usr/sbin/opendmarc global_pid: 8020 kernel: 4.8.8-300.fc25.x86_64 pkg_fingerprint: 4089 D8F2 FDB1 9C98 pkg_vendor: Fedora Project runlevel: N 3 type: CCpp uid: 494
Truncated backtrace: Thread no. 1 (5 frames) #0 mlfi_connect at opendmarc.c:1689 #1 st_connectinfo at engine.c:1276 #2 mi_engine at engine.c:409 #3 mi_handle_session at handler.c:45 #4 mi_thread_handle_wrapper at listener.c:600
Created attachment 1224044 File: backtrace
Created attachment 1224045 File: cgroup
Created attachment 1224046 File: core_backtrace
